						<summary>

						<p>Āñjanēyasvāmin temple, west wall, inside the <hi rend="italic">gōpura.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1541, Siddhārthi, Chaitra śu. 10, [1619 A.D. March 15, Monday].</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the construction of <hi rend="italic">gōpura, prākāra,</hi> the steps leading to the pond, shrines for the Saptaṛishis and Varadarāja-perūmaḷ at Ghaṭikāchala by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Chirigirirāju Chiṉṉa-Timmarāja.</p>						

